JinaraAltar.Description: An abyssal altar containing blood crystals and revealing Ji'nara's fate.
JinaraAltar.Name: Afterlife Abyss

JinaraPlaceHoleUnit.Description: Ji'nara's dark energy is flowing out of the abyss from here.
JinaraPlaceHoleUnit.Name: Abyss Beacon

JinaraWarpPrismTransport.Description:
Flying transport. Can load and unload units and control space and time. Can also deploy to create a power field. Only one can exist in battlefield.

Cannot attack.
JinaraWarpPrismTransport.Name: Ark Prism

JinaraWarpPrismPhasing.Description:
Flying transport. Can load and unload units. Can also deploy to create a power field.

Cannot attack.
JinaraWarpPrismPhasing.Name: Ark Prism

JinaraMotherShip.Description: Ji'nara's capital ship. Crimson Space can carry the entire Tal'darim combat force on the move, and warp in Death Fleets to tear apart the enemy's defenses. **can be used against ground and air**
JinaraMotherShip.Name: Crimson Space

JinaraVoidRay.Description:
Area assault craft. Can use Destruction Beam to attack multiple units. Can plunder resources when attacking enemy structure.

Can attack ground and air units.
JinaraVoidRay.Name: Destroyer

JinaraKirovAirship.Description:
Capital ship. Can deal massive area damage and devour Supplicant to gain greater abilities.

Can attack ground and air units.
JinaraKirovAirship.Name: Doom Engine

JinaraAssimilator.Description: Warped in over a Vespene Geyser to allow harvesting of vespene gas.
JinaraAssimilator.Name: Assimilator

JinaraCyberneticsCore.Description:
Contain upgrades for Herald and Ark Prism.

Enables:
- Herald
-Slaughter
-Blood Hunter
- Enderwalker
JinaraCyberneticsCore.Name: Doom Core

JinaraDarkShrine.Description:
Blood Hunter Technology Structure.

Enables:
- Blood Hunter
JinaraDarkShrine.Name: Blood Shrine

JinaraForge.Description:
Contains weapon and armor upgrades for Protoss air units, Ji'nara, and Crimson Space.

Enable:
- Doom Cannon
JinaraForge.Name: Doom Forge

JinaraWarpGate.Description:
Warps in Ji'nara ground units.

Enables:
- Supplicants
JinaraWarpGate.Name: Doom Warpgate

JinaraMonitor.Description:
Robotic support unit. Can enhance the combat abilities of allied units.

Cannot attack.
Detector
JinaraMonitor.Name: Herald

JinaraSlayer.Description:
Ranged attack strider. Can use Soul Ascension.

Can attack ground and air units.
JinaraSlayer.Name: Slaughter

JinaraDarkTemplar.Description:
Deadly warrior-assassin. Can use Soul Ascension.

Can attack ground units.
JinaraDarkTemplar.Name: Blood Hunter

JinaraAscendant.Description: Potent psionic master. Can use Psionic Orb, Mind Blast, and Sacrifice.**Can attack ground units**
JinaraAscendant.Name: Ascendant

JinaraAvenger.Description: Potent psionic master. Can use Vengeance Granted, Ghast Orb, and Sacrifice.**Can attack ground units**
JinaraAvenger.Name: Martyr

JinaraSupplicant.Description:
Short range warrior. Sacrifices itself to heal Ji'nara when she is near death. Supplicants are warped in two at a time.
**Can attack ground units**
JinaraSupplicant.Name: Supplicant

JinaraNexus.Description:
Primary structure. Can receive gathered resources. Can use the Chrono Boost ability.

Enable:
- Probe
JinaraNexus.Name: Doom Nexus

JinaraProbe.Description: Basic worker unit. Can gather resources and warp in Protoss structures. Can cause massive damage through Detonate. **Can attack ground units**
JinaraProbe.Name: Probe

JinaraPylon.Description:
Provide supply for Protoss forces.
Increase the unit number limit.
Provide power field for the structure, but cannot be used by other Protoss commanders.
JinaraPylon.Name: Blood Pylon

JinaraPhotonCannon.Description:
Primary defensive structure. It can be garrisoned with probes.

Can attack ground and air units.
Detector
JinaraPhotonCannon.Name: Doom Cannon

JinaraRoboticsBay.Description: Blood Hunter and Enderwalker Tech Structure.
JinaraRoboticsBay.Name: Blood Altar

JinaraTwilightCouncil.Description: Contain upgrades for Supplicants and Slaughter.
JinaraTwilightCouncil.Name: Psyche Council

JinaraRoboticsFacility.Description:
Warps in Ji'nara mech units.

Enables:
- Ark Prism
JinaraRoboticsFacility.Name: Doom Robotics Facility

JinaraColossus.Description: Battle strider with a powerful single target attack. Can walk up and down cliffs. **Can attack ground units**
JinaraColossus.Name: Enderwalker

JinaraTemplarArchive.Description:
Ascendant and Martyr Technology Structure.

Enables:
- Ascendant
- Martyr
JinaraTemplarArchive.Name: Forsaken Archive

JinaraAbadon.Description: Unit born from Dark Ritual. Can release powerful dark energy to attack from a distance. **can be used against ground and air**
JinaraAbadon.Name: Demon Host

JinaraAzazle.Description: Unit born from Dark Ritual. Can cause area damage to nearby units. **can be used against ground and air**
JinaraAzazle.Name: Calamity Butler

JinaraNormal.Description: First Ascendant of the Tal'darim. Ji'nara choosing this path specializes in casting spells from a distance, using her surging energy to destroy her enemies. **Can attack ground and air units**
JinaraNormal.Name: Ji'nara

JinaraScarlet.Description:
First Ascendant of the Tal'darim. Ji'nara choosing this path has been corrupted by the Dark God and The Heretics. She will harvest and devour the blood and soul of all life in front of her.

Can attack ground and air units.
JinaraScarlet.Name: Ji'nara

JinaraSoulSupplicant.Description: Unit born from Dark Ritual. Can provide Sanity to other abyssal avatar. **Can attack ground and air units**
JinaraSoulSupplicant.Name: Dark Offering
